Certain characters have a special meaning in CRM Analytics.
Single quote: Encloses a dataset column name in a predicate expression.
Double quote: Encloses a string value or field value in a predicate expression.
Parentheses: Enforces the order in which to evaluate a predicate expression.
Dollar sign: Identifies the Salesforce object in a predicate expression.
Period: Separates the object name and field name in a predicate expression.
